x4freetext: -The neutron scattering corrections were derived by
the Monte-Carlo method using the computer code MCNP.
The low-energy neutron corrections were deduced
using a representation of the neutron spectrum,
evaluated cross sections for the monitor reactions,
and estimates of the unknown technetium cross section
shape. The neutron spectrum determined by time-of-
flight measurement was transformed into a few group
representation which was then adjusted by an
application of the generalized least-squares method
that employed measured reaction rates for several
monitor reactions. Final cross sections were deduced
from the cross ratios and values for the primary
standards. In those cases where measurements were
made relative to secondary standards or to relative
neutron fluence monitors, the data were normalized to
the primary standards by specific ratio measurements
of the secondary standards to the primary standards
or by calibration of the relative monitors to these
